{"title":"{{< i18n wbs_label >}}","markdown":{"headingText":"{{< i18n wbs_label >}}","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n## Purpose of This Document\n\nThis document defines the **Work Breakdown Structure (WBS)** for the project,\ndecomposing the authorized scope into manageable work packages.\n\nThe WBS:\n\n- Is **deliverable-oriented**\n- Covers **100% of project scope**\n- Is aligned with **ecological value as the primary driver**\n- Serves as the foundation for Schedule, Cost, and Resource planning\n\nThis artifact is mandatory **before the Project Management Plan (PMP)**.\n\n---\n\n## WBS – Hierarchical Structure (PMBOK Core)\n\n### Level 1 → Project\n\n**1.0 Subsea Benthic Analysis AI Project**\n\n---\n\n### Level 2 → Phases / Major Deliverables\n\n- **1.1 Initiation & Strategy**\n- **1.2 Governance & Value Management**\n- **1.3 Data & Environmental Preparation**\n- **1.4 AI Model Development**\n- **1.5 Validation & Ecological Assurance**\n- **1.6 Digital Asset Consolidation**\n- **1.7 Project Management & Control**\n\n---\n\n### Level 3 → Work Packages\n\n#### 1.1 Initiation & Strategy\n\n- 1.1.1 Project Charter\n- 1.1.2 Business Case\n- 1.1.3 Strategy & Governance (Value Stream, OKRs)\n- 1.1.4 Stakeholder Identification\n\n#### 1.2 Governance & Value Management\n\n- 1.2.1 OKR Definition & Alignment\n- 1.2.2 KPI Definition & Baseline\n- 1.2.3 Stage‑Gate Framework\n- 1.2.4 Governance Reviews\n\n#### 1.3 Data & Environmental Preparation\n\n- 1.3.1 AUV Image Ingestion\n- 1.3.2 Metadata & Spatial Data Preparation\n- 1.3.3 Image Quality Assessment\n- 1.3.4 Environmental Annotation Guidelines\n\n#### 1.4 AI Model Development\n\n- 1.4.1 Annotation & Labeling (HITL)\n- 1.4.2 Feature Engineering\n- 1.4.3 Model Training (Binary Classification)\n- 1.4.4 Model Inference Pipeline\n\n#### 1.5 Validation & Ecological Assurance\n\n- 1.5.1 Model Performance Evaluation\n- 1.5.2 Ecological Validation by SMEs\n- 1.5.3 Error Analysis & Mitigation\n- 1.5.4 MVP Ecological Acceptance\n\n#### 1.6 Digital Asset Consolidation\n\n- 1.6.1 Dataset Versioning\n- 1.6.2 Model Artifact Management\n- 1.6.3 Traceability & Audit Support\n- 1.6.4 Reuse Readiness Assessment\n\n#### 1.7 Project Management & Control\n\n- 1.7.1 Planning & Monitoring\n- 1.7.2 Risk & Issue Management\n- 1.7.3 Communication & Reporting\n- 1.7.4 Closure & Lessons Learned\n\n---\n\n## Visual Representation 1 — WBS Tree (Conceptual)\n\n```\n1.0 Subsea Benthic Analysis AI\n├── 1.1 Initiation & Strategy\n├── 1.2 Governance & Value\n├── 1.3 Data & Environment\n├── 1.4 AI Development\n├── 1.5 Ecological Validation\n├── 1.6 Digital Assets\n└── 1.7 Project Management\n```\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart TB\n  A[\"1.0 Subsea Benthic Analysis AI Project\"]\n\n  A --> B[\"1.1 Initiation & Strategy\"]\n  A --> C[\"1.2 Governance & Value Management\"]\n  A --> D[\"1.3 Data & Environmental Preparation\"]\n  A --> E[\"1.4 AI Model Development\"]\n  A --> F[\"1.5 Validation & Ecological Assurance\"]\n  A --> G[\"1.6 Digital Asset Consolidation\"]\n  A --> H[\"1.7 Project Management & Control\"]\n\n  B --> B1[\"Charter & Business Case\"]\n  B --> B2[\"Strategy & OKRs\"]\n  B --> B3[\"Stakeholder Register\"]\n\n  D --> D1[\"AUV Image Ingestion\"]\n  D --> D2[\"Metadata & Spatial Data\"]\n  D --> D3[\"Image Quality Assessment\"]\n  D --> D4[\"Environmental Annotation Guidelines\"]\n\n  E --> E1[\"Annotation (HITL)\"]\n  E --> E2[\"Model Training\"]\n  E --> E3[\"Inference Pipeline\"]\n\n  F --> F1[\"Ecological Validation (SME)\"]\n  F --> F2[\"Error Analysis\"]\n  F --> F3[\"MVP Acceptance\"]\n\n  G --> G1[\"Dataset Versioning\"]\n  G --> G2[\"Model Artifacts\"]\n  G --> G3[\"Audit & Traceability\"]\n```\n\n\n---\n\n## Visual Representation 2 — Value-Oriented WBS (Ecology-First)\n\n```\nEcological Confidence\n     │\n     ├── Environmental Data Preparation (1.3)\n     ├── Ecological Validation (1.5)\n     │\n     └── AI as Enabler\n           ├── Annotation & Model (1.4)\n           └── Digital Assets (1.6)\n```\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart TB\n  ECO[\"Ecological Confidence & Environmental Protection\"]\n\n  ECO --> P1[\"Environmental Data Preparation\"]\n  ECO --> P2[\"Ecological Validation & Assurance\"]\n\n  P1 --> D1[\"AUV Image Ingestion\"]\n  P1 --> D2[\"Quality & Noise Reduction\"]\n\n  P2 --> V1[\"SME Validation\"]\n  P2 --> V2[\"False-Negative Control\"]\n\n  ECO --> EN[\"AI as Strategic Enabler\"]\n\n  EN --> A1[\"AI Model Development\"]\n  EN --> A2[\"Automated Screening\"]\n  EN --> A3[\"Digital Asset Creation\"]\n\n  A3 --> L1[\"Reusable Environmental Intelligence\"]\n```\n\n**Interpretation:**  \n\nAI exists to scale ecological understanding, not the reverse.\n\n---\n\n## Visual Representation 3 — WBS × OKR/KR Mapping (Excerpt)\n\n| WBS Element | OKR / KR Supported |\n|-----------|--------------------|\n| 1.3 Data Preparation | KR3, KR5 |\n| 1.4 AI Development | KR1, KR2, KR3 |\n| 1.5 Ecological Validation | KR3 (Primary) |\n| 1.6 Digital Assets | KR4, KR5 |\n| 1.7 Project Control | All KRs |\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart LR\n  W1[\"1.3 Data Preparation\"]\n  W2[\"1.4 AI Development\"]\n  W3[\"1.5 Ecological Validation\"]\n  W4[\"1.6 Digital Assets\"]\n\n  KR1[\"KR1<br/>Expert Focus\"]\n  KR2[\"KR2<br/>Faster Environmental Insight\"]\n  KR3[\"KR3<br/>Ecological Data Protection\"]\n  KR4[\"KR4<br/>Cross-Field Consistency\"]\n  KR5[\"KR5<br/>Reusable Environmental Asset\"]\n\n  W1 --> KR3\n  W1 --> KR5\n\n  W2 --> KR1\n  W2 --> KR2\n  W2 --> KR3\n\n  W3 --> KR3\n\n  W4 --> KR4\n  W4 --> KR5\n```\n\n---\n\n## WBS Governance Rules\n\n- Every WBS element must support at least one KR\n- No work package may proceed without ecological validation where applicable\n- Changes to WBS require formal change control\n\n---\n\n## WBS Baseline\n\nThis WBS becomes the **scope baseline** upon approval and is the authoritative\nreference for:\n\n- Schedule development\n- Cost estimation\n- Resource planning\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":true,"code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true,"format-links":["html","pdf"]},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","metadata-files":["../location/pt.yml"],"toc":true,"css":["../styles.css"],"html-math-method":"mathjax","embed-resources":true,"output-file":"wbs.html"},"language":{"toc-title-document":"Índice","toc-title-website":"Nesta página","related-formats-title":"Outros formatos","related-notebooks-title":"Notebooks","source-notebooks-prefix":"Fonte","other-links-title":"Outros Links","code-links-title":"Ligações de código","launch-dev-container-title":"Iniciar Dev Container","launch-binder-title":"Iniciar Binder","article-notebook-label":"Caderno do Artigo","notebook-preview-download":"Baixar Caderno","n